-- Zoom Integration Update Needs -> SYS-0016 (general, 2026-02-17)
INSERT INTO notes (organization_id, initiative_id, note_text, note_type, author, created_at) SELECT '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001', '999c2ac4-3f54-4461-88c0-0c363dbdd3e2', 'Email from Aman Bali: We were referred to you regarding planned enhancements for the Cerner Zoom integration at Dignity Health. We understand you were involved in code changes for this workflow that were tested successfully but never moved to production around 3-4 years back.

Background: We are currently working to decommission Axway APIM by March and migrate all APIs to Mulesoft. The Cerner Telehealth integration is one of the final pieces remaining on Axway. While the Mulesoft development is complete, we have identified necessary changes on the consumer side (backend .NET code).

In consulting with Gregg and Orlando, we discovered that several enhancements made 3-4 years ago were never deployed to production. Unfortunately, it is not possible to revert these components due to inadequate source code management tools used at that time, to focus solely on the Axway-to-Mulesoft migration. Consequently, we cannot move away from Axway without also deploying these legacy enhancements.

Given the limited timeframe, we need to find a way to test these changes and workflows to ensure there is no impact on the telehealth service. Your insights on how to proceed with testing would be greatly appreciated. Let me know if a meeting is needed to align on this. 

Reid and Bree, I have copied you for your awareness.
', 'general', 'Marty Koepke', '2026-02-17T22:04:32.21+00:00' WHERE NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM notes WHERE initiative_id = '999c2ac4-3f54-4461-88c0-0c363dbdd3e2' AND note_text = 'Email from Aman Bali: We were referred to you regarding planned enhancements for the Cerner Zoom integration at Dignity Health. We understand you were involved in code changes for this workflow that were tested successfully but never moved to production around 3-4 years back.

Background: We are currently working to decommission Axway APIM by March and migrate all APIs to Mulesoft. The Cerner Telehealth integration is one of the final pieces remaining on Axway. While the Mulesoft development is complete, we have identified necessary changes on the consumer side (backend .NET code).

In consulting with Gregg and Orlando, we discovered that several enhancements made 3-4 years ago were never deployed to production. Unfortunately, it is not possible to revert these components due to inadequate source code management tools used at that time, to focus solely on the Axway-to-Mulesoft migration. Consequently, we cannot move away from Axway without also deploying these legacy enhancements.

Given the limited timeframe, we need to find a way to test these changes and workflows to ensure there is no impact on the telehealth service. Your insights on how to proceed with testing would be greatly appreciated. Let me know if a meeting is needed to align on this. 

Reid and Bree, I have copied you for your awareness.
' AND created_at = '2026-02-17T22:04:32.21+00:00');
